# Framework Pass 2 - Refinement Manifest

<audit_manifest>
  <audit_type>framework_pass2</audit_type>

  <purpose>
    Strict second-pass refinement: minimize token load, compress files, strengthen hierarchical rules, remove redundancy, align tags.
  </purpose>

  <scope>
    - Audit and compress root governance files
    - Harden hierarchical loading logic
    - Remove non-essential content
    - Align all tags with TAGS.md definitions
  </scope>

  <constraints>
    - Do NOT increase verbosity
    - Do NOT regenerate from scratch
    - Only refine, compress, optimize
    - Each file absorbable in < 5 seconds of LLM attention
  </constraints>

  <required_inputs>
    - All root governance files
    - All folder-level CLAUDE.md and manifest.md files
    - TAGS.md definitions
  </required_inputs>

  <expected_outputs>
    - Compressed governance files
    - Strengthened scope limitations
    - Removed duplicated tag definitions
    - Short diff or bullet summary per file
  </expected_outputs>

  <activation_conditions>
    - After Pass 1 completion
    - Periodic governance cleanup
  </activation_conditions>

  <run_pattern>
    1. Audit each root file for redundancy
    2. Convert prose to bullet rules
    3. Strengthen "DO NOT LOAD" rules
    4. Trim sections, align tags
    5. Output minimal diffs only
  </run_pattern>
</audit_manifest>
